To further alleviate the size problem of the InfantBooks corpus, we also introduced the C4-easy corpus, based on filtering via the Flesch reading-ease score (FRE). However, good readability is more of a necessary than a sufficient condition for inferring that content is intended for children, in other words, if there were not the results on InfantBooks, the positive results on C4-easy in isolation only proved a related hypothesis (``easier texts are the key to commonsense''), not the original one (``children texts are the key'').